&lt;p&gt;As you know (if not, probably the following lines gives you an idea), &lt;strong&gt;vIPer&lt;/strong&gt; was originally designed to export from &lt;em&gt;ipynb&lt;/em&gt; files to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a plain static html&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a slideshow powered by Landslide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the last release, &lt;strong&gt;IPython&lt;/strong&gt; support this kind of exportation using the well designed and easily extensible &lt;code&gt;IPython.nbconvert&lt;/code&gt; library. Now, it is easier to incorporate the IPython machinery inside vIPer and support the exportation to several formats. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class="more"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.damian.oquanta.info/posts/viper-is-now-using-ipythonnbconvert.html"&gt;Read more…&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>python</category><category>IPython</category><category>vIPer</category><category>nbconvert</category><category>threads</category><guid>http://www.damian.oquanta.info/posts/viper-is-now-using-ipythonnbconvert.html</guid><pubDate>Tue, 24 Sep 2013 22:02:38 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Improving vIPer slideshows styling</title><link>http://www.damian.oquanta.info/posts/improving-viper-slideshows-styling.html</link><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The last weekend, I had some time to improve the styling of the slideshow view (of the IPython notebook) rendered by vIPer.&lt;/p&gt;
